@thelistshowtv  interviewed me and asked me for some tips to give parents whose children’s are returning back to school after remote learning.

Things are constantly changing and I don’t have all of the answers but hopefully some of these tips are helpful to you :)

node.text:
☝🏽💤
Day 1 of my 8th (technically 9th) first day of kindergarten is done!

I met 7 of my new kinders and will meet 6 more tomorrow.

Along with the activities in this reel we did a lot of practicing procedures.
We talked about how to properly use materials, took a tour of our school, and made it home safely 🙌🏽

I hope you all had a beautiful day!
.
.
.

node.text:
🌈🥰
Tomorrow is the first day of our soft start week.
I will have a few of my students Monday - Thursday this week.

I left Friday evening feeling good about how much I accomplished.

Right now I’m focused on enjoying my Sunday.

I hope you all have an amazing week.

node.text:
⏮📆
2 years ago I didn’t know that not only would this be my last in person meet the teacher but it would also be the last one in my first classroom ever.

I didn’t know that a virus would come and flip our worlds upside down and in the midst of chaos I would accept a position teaching kindergarten at a new school in a new district.

I didn’t know that my mom who has come to support me at every open house since my first year wouldn’t be able to come for the next 2 years.

I didn’t know all of these big changes were coming and I don’t know what is next.

But what I do know is that I’m right where I am suppose to be.

Today I had virtual orientation and I got to see the faces of my new kinders and their families.

I stayed later than I should have at school and made sure that I left feeling good.

I know that this year will have its challenges but I also know that magic can still happen even through the toughest times.

I am tired but I am not anxious (at this moment lol)

I am going to enjoy this moment of peace this Friday evening and pray that it trickles through the weekend and stays present through our first week of school.

Year 8 here I come!

node.text:
🍬🍪
The cookie jar has retired
But the candy jar is here!

And it’s obviously rainbow for my class 🤣🌈

Y’all we aren’t going to talk about the amount of extra this was… i just couldn’t see one of the first things I purchased for my house go to waste 🙃🤷🏽‍♀️

My dad and brother won’t be stealing cookies out of the cookie jar anymore but my kinders will be enjoying our rainbow jar this year 💕

Thanks @maniacsinthemiddle for inspiring me with your jolly ranchers 
.
.
.

✌🏽✔️
Today was our first official day back and my second day getting my room together.

I am all moved into my new classroom, pretty much unpacked and the base of my bulletin boards are done 👏🏽🙌🏽

Tomorrow morning is filled with meetings but I’m hoping to get some more done in the afternoon.

I’m feeling really good 💕🥰

☀️✌🏽
Thank you Summer 2021!

Tomorrow is my first official day back to work.

Today’s message at church was everything I needed to get me in the right head space for tomorrow.

I feel at peace and ready for this week!

I’m so thankful this summer!
It was everything I knew I needed.

node.text:
🤎🍪
Just a girl and a gallon of cookies!

After almost 4 years (new cookies i promise lol) these cookies jars that became a staple in my kitchen are finding a new home 🤣

I will miss being asked
“How do you get them some perfect?” and
“do you even eat them?” 🤣🤣
but they will have a new home
and purpose now 🙌🏽

Any guesses on where this jar will go and what treasures it will hold?

Ps.
If you’re new here I’m not us usually this weird lol. But i did really love these jars.
